social_posts.post_text:
🇨🇺CUBA🇨🇺… Ending the year with an incredible adventure. My dad @tex.schneider.photography invited me to go with him on a photography workshop to my bucket list country, Cuba. In my many international travels THIS makes my top overall best experience. I have so much to share but right now I feel grateful to have encountered this incredible country while leaving with a massive respect for the people and their culture. More on my stories.

Thank you to @yourcubatravel for curating a breathtaking and very special experience. 

Special thanks to @1timestopper @ems_photo_adventures @bettyinhavana @madrinaeg

I absolutely love using cute socks when gifting a bottle of wine. It’s so easy! 🧦 #ButterCab and #ButterChardonnay by @JamCellars are my delicious go-to favorites 🍷+ so easy to love. You can find them at any local grocery store for under $20 a bottle. Hope you all have a happy and healthy New Year. CHEERS! 🎉 #JaMPartner #ad

2022: A year of extreme highs & lows. Exploring parts of Spain and Portugal is something I’ll never forget. There were also many unexpected hospital visits with major surgery and two months recovery. Couldn’t have done it without the support of my parents, close friends, and my cat who played nurse. 😹 Ended the year with the ultimate high - a trip to Cuba with my dad @tex.schneider.photography. This year proved to be an adventurous one, despite health hiccups. Very happy and grateful. Cheers to a new year with new possibilities! 💫

Thank you to @jan_schneider__ and @tex.schneider.photography for being the real superhero this year. I have the best parents. 🫶

When we were in Havana, Cuba, we had the opportunity to shoot these beautiful ballerinas in this gorgeous drying room. It was an incredible experience. 🩰 

Special thanks: @yourcubatravel @1timestopper @ems_photo_adventures

Basically using this image as my visual “out of office” reply. I’m currently spending quality time in Italy - can’t wait to share more! I also recently leased this image to a popular greeting card company so if you see “Shadow Girl” at your local card stand, I’d love to know! ✌️Ciao!

Milan in February. I absolutely love this city. ❤️

PC: @thetravelrose 🤍

Sending extra love to those who might be feeling a little low on this day. Romance isn’t everything but your value as an individual is. And to those who are happy and thriving, I wish you many more years of bliss. 💗

Hello from Venice. I’m off to stuff my face with pasta. 👋

Yesterday was my birthday and turning a year older isn’t so terrible when you’re in Venice during Carnival season. 🎭 There’s a certain magic to this place - sharing more on my stories. And yes, that last image is me sitting on a bridge like a tourist.. it’s my birthday, I’m allowed to be cringy.

Carnival is officially over and what an experience it was! This kind of content isn’t what I typically post but I was captivated by the costumes and the sheer gregariousness of it all. People travel to Venice from all over the world to participate in carnival, it’s hard not to be swept away by the magic. Some of these costumes are a true work of art. 🎭 I’ll create a story highlight under bio. 

Images were taken on my @leica_camera #leicaq

My weekend plans involve me kickin’ up my heels and opening up my favorite #ButterChardonnay by @JaMCellars. This has been my go-wine for years and is so perfectly creamy, rich and bold while still feeling light and refreshing. Have you tried it? 🍷🙃

I snuck in a few cat pics for your viewing pleasure. 🐈

All images taken with @leica_camera #leicaq

Happy PRIDE!! 🏳️‍🌈 Earlier in the month I was able to crack open a few bottles of #ButterBubbles by @JaMCellars to share with friends. Perfectly crisp & bubbly that pairs flawlessly with love and authenticity.  No matter what you're celebrating, toast with #ButterBubbles!

#ProudPartner #JaMPartner #JaMCellars

We were on tropical storm watch yesterday, this was a first for me as well as many Southern Californians. Luckily, it didn’t do any damage in my area but it did hit hard in mountain and high desert areas. With fires and hurricanes happening simultaneously, I’m hoping everyone stays safe out there!

📍Images taken when I was inside a cab during a tropical rain storm in Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam. I remember observing how the passing colors looked abstract, like pretty blobs of paint.

I (FINALLY) saw the Barbie movie and it reminded me of a project I did awhile back where I covered this blue thunderbird with pink Post-it Notes and turned it into the pink @barbie convertible of my DREAMS!  This was extremely time consuming as you can imagine but it was SO fun to execute. I had permission to shoot in front of the famous Paul Smith pink wall and it caused quite a crowd (wish I had video footage).

Shockingly, I know the EXACT number of Post-it Notes I used to cover the whole car - yes I counted! 😅 It might be fun to do a guessing content if anyone is interested. 

(Past work for @postit / @3m) 
Also shout out to my mom who helped me with this wild project.

I’m soaking up the last month of summer with delicious Butter Bubbles by @JaMCellars! These bubbles are my go-to and my secret is adding a squeeze of citrus to give it that added summer taste. Cheers! 🥂🍊 #JaMPartner

It’s not difficult to fall in love with Lisbon, Portugal. We had a pleasant walk through Pink Street and soaked in all the color and unique exteriors. If you’re interested in shooting here I highly recommend visiting early in the day before the afternoon crowd takes over. 🩷

Although most of us are ready for fall, it still feels like summer in Palm Springs! ☀️ I’m soaking in all the sunshine and sipping on #ButterCans by @JaMCellars! I’ve been a big fan of the brand long before working with them and this #ButterChardonnay is my favorite to sip outside. 😋 Grab some for yourself under $20 at your local grocery store or delivered to your door! #JaMPartner jamcellars.com/locate

Happy first weekend in 2024! I’ve apparently made a habit of ringing in the new year sick - addicted to soup and DayQuil. I’m excited to be sneeze-free and back in the studio hopefully sooner than later. Just wanted to pop in and say hello and happy 2024! 💥

Images are of my visit to the Gucci Gardens in Florence.
